<p align="center"><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">English Translation</span></strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;"> </span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: small;">For  the sake of thin-waisted fish-eyed Nappinnai dame, the Lord of cloud  hue, my master, battled angrily and subdued the seven mighty  dust-raising bulls. By the penance of Bhagiratha, the river flows  splitting dark mountain rocks and pushing elephants; down the slopes on  the banks of the Ganga, He resides in Vadari-Ashrama.</span></p></div><span class="article_separator">&nbsp;</span>
